-- Blackleg Disease Found in Calves in Russia’s South, Service Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-03-16T07:56:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/blackleg-disease-found-in-calves-in-russia-s-south-service-says.html
Nine calves under six months died
of blackleg at a private farm in  Russia ’s south-western Kursk
region, Russia’s food safety service said.  The farm was put into quarantine and the remaining 480 head
of were vaccinated,  Rosselkhoznadzor  said in a statement on its
website. Blackleg, an infectious bacterial disease, was last
reported in the Kursk region in 1952, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
